                <h2>WHAT IS THE VISION OF THE REPUBLIC?</h2>
                <p>
                    We believe there is a better way to manage society other than through the use of debt financial systems.
                    We can not claim to have a solution, however, it is what we are striving towards.
                </p>

                <h2>WHAT IS THE PURPOSE OF THE REPUBLIC?</h2>
                <p>
                    The idea behind the republic is to provide a vehicle for a people to use in order to take a stand
                    against debt monetary systems. We are pro-a-good-and-sensible-republic managing a society based on
                    equality, and a big part of this is to ensure that the energy system we choose to use (our means of exchange)
                    empowers and uplifts all people.
                </p>
                <p>
                    In a sentence: we are creating a world without debt.
                </p>
                <h2>WHERE IS THE REPUBLIC LOCATED ON A MAP?</h2>
                <p>
                    The republic is an <em>artificial person</em> (like all nations and governments), there is nothing to visit, no geography to
                    point out and certainly no ground to walk upon. It is not possible to stand in the legal substance of any country
                    as a "people", in order to enter a countries substance (jurisdiction) you must act as its citizen (a <em>persona</em>).
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you take the time to read various nations statute and acts,
                    you will notice that when it comes to defining the borders of a nation, legally speaking, it is more often
                    than not, vague and contradictory. Essentially a nation exercises jurisdiction by consent, and in the absence of
                    consent, it has no jurisdiction (think contractual relationship).
                </p>
                <h2>WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE REPUBLIC AND A TRADITIONAL STATE?</h2>
                <p>
                    The republic is 100% voluntary and 100% debt free. Our aim is to provide services using private
                    capital (debt and interest free energy) in order to build the things we need without burdening
                    the people. And if you don't ike the way it all works, you
                    are free to leave. And leaving simply means, no longer using its services and identifying
                    with its brand.
                </p>
                <p>
                    A traditional state on the other hand, imposes and inserts itself between you and the people you wish to
                    interact with. You could look at a traditional Citizen as a type of tax cattle for a government that
                    serves as an interface between the purveyors of interest (parasites who make their money through usurious
                    means) and you. As an example, a state that borrows excessively to produce things that the citizenry donâ€™t
