                <h2>HOW DO I REGISTER MY CAR WITH THE REPUBLIC?</h2>
                <p>
                    The republic does not "register" anything in the public, services are limited to a "record" of private property and the
                    verification of that record should the need arise. How you choose to use your record is up to you and you take full responsibility
                    for your actions and any consequences that may arise from them.
                </p>
                <h2>CAN I GET MARRIED IN THE REPUBLIC?</h2>
                <p>
                    The republic is more than happy to record a union between two people. However, you may wish to carefully consider
                    your options before deciding a course of action.
                </p>
                <h2>HOW DO I RECORD MY NEW BORN'S BIRTH?</h2>
                <p>
                    Before a <em>persona</em> can be "recorded", you will need to provide proof of birth which should
                    be signed by at least two medical practitioners (witnesses). In addition to this, you will need to provide the
                    name that you gift to your new born (affidavit). Once this has been received, you will have the opportunity to
                    create an express trust, the asset of which is the title to the new born's name. From this you are issued with
                    a birth certificate which reflects our record of the full legal persona or citizen.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Please note that the birth record we offer is a private record. It does not replace a record you may wish to use
                    with a traditional nation state. While we believe registering a birth in the traditional sense offers your new born's energy
                    as collateral to current and future debts, it is up to you to make an informed decision as to what you wish to do.
                </p>
                <h2>HOW DO I OBTAIN AN ID DOCUMENT AND PASSPORT?</h2>
                <p>
                    In order to obtain a passport and ID document, you must go through a similar process to that of a new born.
                    You will need to provide affidavits of your given name and your claim to its title. Once received
                    you will have an opportunity to create an express trust with title of the name as an asset of trust.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Once you have completed the process, the private documentation will be made available to your account pages.
                </p>
